This is an enumerated integer that defines the current power status of the hardware item. Values include:
0: Unknown 1: Not Applicable 2: No Power Applied 3: Full Power Applied 4: Power Save - Normal 5: Power Save - Degraded 6: Power Save - Standby 7: Power Save - Critical 8: Power Save - Low Power Mode 9: Power Save - Unknown 10: Power Cycle 11: Power Warning 12: Power Off
Value 1 means that the hardware item doesn't require the direct application of power (e.g., a but or bolt). If the value for this item is 3, then the PowerCapability class will describe the particular power requirements of this item through the HasPower association. This is an optional attribute.
